                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/oo/edit/master/knpu/episode4/autoloading-awesomeness.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Have you ever heard of an autoloader? Even if you <em>have</em>, you might not know what
they do or how they work.</p>
<h2 id="what-does-an-autoloader-do">What does an Autoloader Do? <a class="headerlink" href="autoloading-awesomeness#what-does-an-autoloader-do" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Autoloaders change everything. In PHP, you can't reference a class or a function
unless you - or someone - requires or includes that file first. That's why - in
<code>bootstrap.php</code> - we have a <code>require</code> statement for <em>every</em> file:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="864c71359b">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-20" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
