</p>
<p>Notice I put <em>two</em> back-slashes. Since this is the escape character, if you only
have one, it looks like you're escaping the next quote character. So, to get one slash,
we need to use two - it's an ugly detail. Anyways, replace backslashes with a forward slash
and pass that the class name. Finally, add the <code>.php</code> at the end.</p>
<p>Just in case, check to see if that file exists. If it does, <code>require $path</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="1c80f71ef7">
